Package: flexTab1
Title: Creation of a Table 1 and descriptive summary tables
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Katja", "Gutmair", , "katja.gutmair@ibe.med.uni-muenchen.de", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0002-3948-6186"))
Description: This package provides functions for quickly generating summary statistics for both 
             categorical and numeric variables, either for a single group or stratified across 
             multiple groups, in a nice output format ("Table 1"). The key advantage of this package is its 
             flexibility: users can choose from a wide range of summary measures (e.g., median, 
             mean, standard deviation, and more). Additionally, options are available 
             to visualize the frequency of missing values per variable, p-values and/or standardized 
             mean differences. Users can also decide whether to output a publication-ready table 
             using the flextable package or a simple data frame for further customization of the layout.
